@adamreeve @wjlutter actually I think I just figured out what the problem is. 

in types.py, DaqMxRawData is defined as size=2 and of type np.int16. this works for 16-bit ADCs, as all the data for each sample is contained within 2 bytes. However, for a 24-bit ADC, the size has to increase to 4 / np.int32. So it gets everything approximately right for the first channel (gets the first 16 bits) but completely messes up the second channel (grabs the last 16 bits of the first channel instead of the first 16 bits of the second channel). And so on and so forth for additional channels.

Unfortunately, it doesn't appear that the DaqMxRawData type is specific enough to differentiate between the two data sizes. Additionally, it seems like the minimum raw_data_width, even for a single 16-bit ADC channel, is 4 bytes, which makes doing this programmatically frustrating.

