@jacaicedob Where are you sourcing this file from, the NOAA/NCDC HAS server you mentioned or another source.  The HAS server removed any leading padding and should work (partially) with Py-ART 1.6.0.  Other source may include some leading padding which will require a newer version of Py-ART which includes the fix in #540 or a work around.  

You should be able to tell the difference with the command `python -c "f = open('KJAX_SDUS72_EETJAX_201508272205', 'rb'); print(f.read(30))"`.  A "un-padded" file will begin with SDUS74, a padded file will start with something else.  

In either case you will likely need to update you Py-ART version by building from source once #585 is merged.  Instructions for this process can be found in the [README](https://github.com/ARM-DOE/pyart#installing-from-source).

