@erikrose, the discussion I remember in the last week or two about dependency problems was about optional dependencies, which we currently have but will probably remove in the next release (see #3650). I don't think this isn't particularly relevant here.

My main motivation for wanting this PR is #3455 which I linked above. Removing conditional dependencies is the best way I am aware of to fix problems in our wheels. We can easily make our `mock` dependency unconditional, so `argparse` is the only dependency stopping us from removing conditional dependencies entirely. Alternatively, we could start building a separate wheel for Python 2.6, for both the `acme` and `certbot` packages, but I'd like to avoid this if possible.

I'm also not sure what distros are affected. Based on the conversation here, I thought it was an Arch Linux problem. Unless you know the answer here, perhaps I/we should do more testing. If it is just an Arch problem, we could reach out to them and see if they're willing to solve the problem on their end.

