@abrahamrhoffman I think https://github.com/ray-project/ray/issues/1049 can also resolve the issue. After that change, you can wait for resource release by calling `ray.wait()` on a task that shuts down the actor as follows:

```
import ray
@ray.remote(num_gpus=1)
class GPU(object):
    def __init__(self):
        pass

    def kill(self):
       exit(0)


actor1 = GPU.remote()
ray.wait([actor1.kill.remote()])
# resources have been guaranteed to be released
```

