The reason why I mentioned the ffmpeg binary, is because it doesn't belong into the repo here and bloats it up from a few hundred KiB to more than 55 MiB. Since rebasing the master branch is something you don't ever want to do unless you really have to, like right now, I was suggesting to go a step further and remove it as well. It is only used by the Windows installers and can be moved to a different, external location and then loaded in while building the installers. We had a discussion about this a few months ago. As I've said, this requires a change of the commit where it was added and another one (which can be done later) in order to fix the builds. I know it's stupid to discuss it here now and rush the whole thing, but we are forced to act and could at least try to make the best out of this situation. It's optional, though.

